The paper discusses the effect of open access on citation rates, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it deals with the dissemination and access of digital information. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as it deals with the retrieval of information from large datasets. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are less likely but still possible as they deal with the distribution and security of information. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a possibility as it deals with the impact of social networks on information dissemination.
